@page "/org/users"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Users — PartnerConnect</PageTitle>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1 class="page-title">Users</h1>
</div>

@* Per-user identity isn't wired to the org portal yet: the portal authenticates with the org API
   key, and the user model associates users to a dealer/tenant rather than to an organization. So
   there's no org-scoped user list to show today — this is an honest placeholder, not a fake CRUD. *@
<FluentMessageBar Intent="MessageIntent.Info" AllowDismiss="false" Class="page-message">
    Per-user access management arrives with single sign-on.
</FluentMessageBar>

<FluentCard>
    <div class="empty-state">
        <div class="empty-title">User management is coming with SSO</div>
        <div class="empty-sub">
            Today your organization signs in with a shared organization key, so there are no individual
            user accounts to manage here yet. Once single sign-on is enabled you'll be able to invite
            teammates, assign roles (Org Admin, Tenant Manager, Viewer), and scope them to specific
            tenants from this screen.
        </div>
    </div>
</FluentCard>
